Title: Ramboy
Description: On Achill Island in Ireland, Cian hopes to spend the summer playing soccer with his friends. But his grandfather thinks it’s about time to pass down a family tradition.

Title: The Strange $55 Million Saga of a Netflix Series You’ll Never See
Description: After suitors flocked to a sci-fi project by Carl Rinsch, director of a single movie, the winner handed over money and control. They’re still fighting.

Title: Something for Everyone, Even Cannibals, at the Philadelphia Fringe
Description: The festival presents a violent Shakespearean interaction with fruit, dance for neurodiverse and neurotypical audiences and showers of (play) money.

Title: Up the Matildas!
Description: Australia’s national women’s soccer team have walked away with the nation’s hearts clasped firmly in their hands.

Title: How Hokusai’s Art Crashed Over the Modern World
Description: The MFA Boston shows how one of the greatest printmakers, from Edo Japan, inspired a tidal wave of followers, from Gauguin to Lichtenstein.

Title: Your Wednesday Briefing: Trump Pleads Not Guilty
Description: Plus, a pattern of abandoned brides in India.

Title: Two Memoirs of Chinese American Hunger, Three Decades Apart
Description: Fae Myenne Ng’s “Orphan Bachelors” recalls her coming of age in midcentury San Francisco; Jane Wong’s “Meet Me Tonight in Atlantic City” recalls hers in 1980s and ’90s New Jersey.

Title: 9 Furniture Designers From Across the African Diaspora
Description: Jomo Tariku, a designer and data scientist, shines a spotlight on trailblazing industrial artisans and their provocative, inspiring work.

Title: ‘Elyria’ Review: The Past Catches Up to Them, Outside Cleveland
Description: A microcosmic tale of the Indian diaspora, Deepa Purohit’s new play centers on the tangled history of two women and the man in between them.
Date: The Past Catches Up to Them,February 28
